{
    "publish_date": "2012-11-26T18:08:26.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT13M15S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "MATT: OK, so I&#39;m going to\ndo a card trick based", 
            "dur": "1.74", 
            "start": "0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on the number 27.", 
            "dur": "1.69", 
            "start": "1.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this is my all-time favorite\nmaths card trick.", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "3.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;m going to show it for\nyou today, and I&#39;m going to", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "6.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "explain it.", 
            "dur": "1.71", 
            "start": "8.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I found this trick in an old\n1950&#39;s math book written by", 
            "dur": "4.58", 
            "start": "10.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Martin Gardner.", 
            "dur": "1.13", 
            "start": "15.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And for me it is the maths\ncard trick with the most", 
            "dur": "3.36", 
            "start": "16.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "beautiful maths behind it\nout of all of them.", 
            "dur": "2.06", 
            "start": "19.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And because it is a math card\ntrick, it does involve a lot", 
            "dur": "3.356", 
            "start": "21.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of long tedious counting.", 
            "dur": "1.624", 
            "start": "24.946"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But bear with us here.", 
            "dur": "0.94", 
            "start": "26.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this involves 27 cards, so\nI&#39;m going to take 27 off.", 
            "dur": "3.99", 
            "start": "27.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this is a genuine count.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "31.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One, two, three, four, five,\nsix, seven, eight, nine, 10.", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "32.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "27 is actually one of my\nfavorite numbers--", 
            "dur": "1.98", 
            "start": "36.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One, two, three, four, five,\nsix, seven, eight, nine, 10--", 
            "dur": "4.19", 
            "start": "38.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because it&#39;s a cubed number.", 
            "dur": "0.95", 
            "start": "42.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One, two, three, four,\nfive, six, seven.", 
            "dur": "3.44", 
            "start": "43.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, that&#39;s 27 cards.", 
            "dur": "0.62", 
            "start": "47.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And this works with any 27\ncards, and none of this trick", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "47.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is slight-of-hand.", 
            "dur": "1.32", 
            "start": "50.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "None of it is YouTube magic\nwhere I&#39;m using something", 
            "dur": "4.05", 
            "start": "51.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "sneaky, or a sneaky edit.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "55.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;ll explain the trick\nafterwards, so it&#39;s OK.", 
            "dur": "1.88", 
            "start": "57.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But this is how works--", 
            "dur": "0.75", 
            "start": "59.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You get 27 cards, you\nshuffle them up.", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "60.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m actually going to\nget Brady to both", 
            "dur": "2.409", 
            "start": "62.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "film and be the volunteer.", 
            "dur": "1.411", 
            "start": "64.569"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;ll flick through, do you\nwant to tap which one you", 
            "dur": "2.6", 
            "start": "65.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "want, which one of these?", 
            "dur": "1.36", 
            "start": "68.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK that one there.", 
            "dur": "0.45", 
            "start": "69.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do you want to show you\nthe camera that card?", 
            "dur": "1.57", 
            "start": "70.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Don&#39;t let me see\nit, obviously.", 
            "dur": "1.265", 
            "start": "71.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And do you want to put it back\nin wherever you want?", 
            "dur": "3.065", 
            "start": "73.225"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thank you.", 
            "dur": "0.032", 
            "start": "76.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now all he needs to do is just\nremember what that card was,", 
            "dur": "2.548", 
            "start": "76.322"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and believe me, people in the\ncomments will mention", 
            "dur": "1.58", 
            "start": "78.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "afterwards if you don&#39;t.", 
            "dur": "1.01", 
            "start": "80.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Brady what&#39;s your favorite\nnumber from 1 to 27, if you", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "81.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "had to pick a number?", 
            "dur": "1.85", 
            "start": "83.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: 10.", 
            "dur": "0.91", 
            "start": "85.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: 10, any particular\nreason why 10?", 
            "dur": "1.4", 
            "start": "86.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: I just like\nhow it looks.", 
            "dur": "1.446", 
            "start": "88.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: You like it?", 
            "dur": "0.55", 
            "start": "89.556"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK.", 
            "dur": "0.024", 
            "start": "90.106"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Are you looking for your\ncard by the way?", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "90.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What I want you to do is have\na look, and see if you can", 
            "dur": "2.76", 
            "start": "92.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "spot which pile your\ncard goes into.", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "95.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And people may have seen\nthis trick done before.", 
            "dur": "2.86", 
            "start": "97.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s a variation, in fact, it&#39;s\na generalization on a 21", 
            "dur": "3.495", 
            "start": "100.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "card trick.", 
            "dur": "1.075", 
            "start": "104.135"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which pile is it in?", 
            "dur": "1.155", 
            "start": "105.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: It&#39;s in that pile.", 
            "dur": "1.515", 
            "start": "106.365"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: In the middle\npile there?", 
            "dur": "0.65", 
            "start": "107.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, I&#39;m going to pick\nthem up from the", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "108.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "viewer&#39;s right to left.", 
            "dur": "3.26", 
            "start": "111.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what people tend to do is\nthey do this tedious counting", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "114.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "out each time.", 
            "dur": "0.57", 
            "start": "117.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what I&#39;m actually\ndoing is last time I", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "117.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "memorized all the cards.", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "120"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so I when you told me which\npile, I had narrowed it", 
            "dur": "2.74", 
            "start": "121.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "down to nine possible\ncards it could be.", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "124.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If I do it again, because of the\nway I&#39;m dealing it out, if", 
            "dur": "2.54", 
            "start": "127.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you tell me which pile it&#39;s in\nthis time, I will narrow it", 
            "dur": "2.95", 
            "start": "129.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "down to one of three\npossible cards.", 
            "dur": "3.01", 
            "start": "132.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which pile is it in this time?", 
            "dur": "1.42", 
            "start": "135.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: This time it is\nin the middle pile.", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "137.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: The middle one again,\nthere we are.", 
            "dur": "0.71", 
            "start": "139.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK purely coincidence, I&#39;ll\npick them up again.", 
            "dur": "3.73", 
            "start": "139.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then we&#39;ll do it one last\ntime again dividing by 3, and", 
            "dur": "3.11", 
            "start": "143.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this is why 27 is 3 cubed.", 
            "dur": "2.93", 
            "start": "146.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you say which one it&#39;s in I\nwill know, having memorized", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "149.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "all the cards, exactly one in\none, or I will know precisely", 
            "dur": "4.63", 
            "start": "152.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which card it is.", 
            "dur": "1.02", 
            "start": "157.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s just the pure\ninformation of this trick.", 
            "dur": "1.97", 
            "start": "158.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which one&#39;s it in?", 
            "dur": "0.94", 
            "start": "160.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: That one.", 
            "dur": "0.72", 
            "start": "161"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: That one over there.", 
            "dur": "0.27", 
            "start": "161.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cool, OK.", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "161.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So now to be fair all\nof that wasn&#39;t true.", 
            "dur": "3.05", 
            "start": "164.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well the numbers were true,\nand the number of cards it", 
            "dur": "2.77", 
            "start": "167.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "could&#39;ve been going from 27 to\nnine, to three, to one, that", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "170.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is completely accurate.", 
            "dur": "1.09", 
            "start": "173.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I wasn&#39;t bothering to memorize\nthem though, I was doing", 
            "dur": "1.69", 
            "start": "174.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "something else slightly\ndifferent.", 
            "dur": "1.92", 
            "start": "176.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What was your card?", 
            "dur": "0.56", 
            "start": "178.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can tell me now.", 
            "dur": "0.75", 
            "start": "178.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: It was the\nking of hearts.", 
            "dur": "2.04", 
            "start": "179.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: King of hearts, and what\nwas your favorite number?", 
            "dur": "1.635", 
            "start": "181.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: 10.", 
            "dur": "0.725", 
            "start": "183.025"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: OK.", 
            "dur": "0.38", 
            "start": "183.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Watch this.", 
            "dur": "0.4", 
            "start": "184.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here we go.", 
            "dur": "0.35", 
            "start": "184.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Ready?", 
            "dur": "0.58", 
            "start": "184.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One, two, three, four, five,\nsix, seven, eight, nine, 10.", 
            "dur": "5.89", 
            "start": "185.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "King of hearts.", 
            "dur": "1.81", 
            "start": "191.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So this trick, you can put the\ncard-- even though you don&#39;t", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "193.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "know what it is-- as long as\nthey tell you which pile it&#39;s", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "195.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in, you can put it anywhere\nin that deck.", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "198.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if you say any number, after\nthree lots of dealing it", 
            "dur": "3.54", 
            "start": "200.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "out, I can put the card\ninto that position.", 
            "dur": "1.94", 
            "start": "203.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that is my all-time\nfavorite", 
            "dur": "2.78", 
            "start": "205.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "maths based card trick.", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "208.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Do you want to know\nhow it works?", 
            "dur": "0.84", 
            "start": "210.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: Yes please.", 
            "dur": "0.56", 
            "start": "211.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: This is brilliant.", 
            "dur": "0.89", 
            "start": "211.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, so can I have some of\nyour famous brown paper?", 
            "dur": "4.73", 
            "start": "212.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK, excellent.", 
            "dur": "0.82", 
            "start": "217.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now let&#39;s look at why\nthis trick works.", 
            "dur": "3.14", 
            "start": "218.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now you&#39;re going to have\nto bear with me here.", 
            "dur": "3.28", 
            "start": "221.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;m going to set up a\nslightly unusual way", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "224.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to look at the cards.", 
            "dur": "1.21", 
            "start": "226.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because when you get the 27\ncards, the very last step-- if", 
            "dur": "3.5", 
            "start": "227.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we go from the end\nof the trick--", 
            "dur": "1.07", 
            "start": "230.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I pick them up into three\npiles of nine cards.", 
            "dur": "4.41", 
            "start": "232.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "From now on I&#39;m going to call\nthe top one the 0th pile, and", 
            "dur": "3.51", 
            "start": "236.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then the first pile, and\nthe second pile.", 
            "dur": "1.54", 
            "start": "239.94"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And there&#39;s a reason for that\nin a moment, but just bear", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "241.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with me while I set\nup some notation.", 
            "dur": "2.16", 
            "start": "244"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So when the cards go back\ntogether there are nine cards", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "246.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the top pile one, two, three,\nfour, five, six, seven,", 
            "dur": "2.914", 
            "start": "249.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "eight, nine.", 
            "dur": "0.696", 
            "start": "252.894"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that was why I called\nthe 0th pile on top.", 
            "dur": "2.46", 
            "start": "253.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Then there was one, two, three,\nfour, five, six, seven,", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "256.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "eight, nine in the first pile.", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "258.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the bottom one-- one, two,\nthree, four, five, six, seven,", 
            "dur": "2.715", 
            "start": "261.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "eight, nine, that was\nthe second pile.", 
            "dur": "1.785", 
            "start": "263.725"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And as it turns out your one\nwas the king of hearts.", 
            "dur": "3.19", 
            "start": "265.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That ended up being the\n10th card down.", 
            "dur": "4.07", 
            "start": "268.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because you said at the very\nbeginning your favorite number", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "272.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is 10, and your king of\nhearts ended up there.", 
            "dur": "3.46", 
            "start": "275.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so now when you think about\nit these top three from", 
            "dur": "3.55", 
            "start": "278.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the final pile-- because this is\nthe very last top, middle,", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "282.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and bottom pile--", 
            "dur": "1.11", 
            "start": "285.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that top one came from the\nprevious top pile.", 
            "dur": "2.67", 
            "start": "286.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That was the previous 0th pile,\nthat was the previous", 
            "dur": "3.07", 
            "start": "288.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "middle pile, that was the\nprevious bottom pile.", 
            "dur": "3.18", 
            "start": "291.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That was the previous\ntop, middle, bottom.", 
            "dur": "4.055", 
            "start": "295.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Top, middle, bottom.", 
            "dur": "3.09", 
            "start": "302.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so actually if you\nwatch it you can", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "305.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "see how that happens.", 
            "dur": "0.77", 
            "start": "306.42"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because I&#39;ve picked them up\nfrom the second time.", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "307.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ve got the top, the middle,\nand the bottom packets.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "309.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Each are nine cards, I&#39;ve\nput them together.", 
            "dur": "1.97", 
            "start": "311.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I deal out the next three piles,\nand the first three", 
            "dur": "3.57", 
            "start": "313.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "come from that top\npack of nine.", 
            "dur": "2.13", 
            "start": "316.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then the next three come\nfrom that top pack of nine,", 
            "dur": "2.66", 
            "start": "319.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and then the next three from\nthe same top pack of nine.", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "321.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that&#39;s why over here the\ntop three come from the", 
            "dur": "2.84", 
            "start": "323.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "previous top 0th pile.", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "326.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The next three of each one come\nfrom the middle pile.", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "329.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that&#39;s the first three off\nthe middle, next three off the", 
            "dur": "2.97", 
            "start": "331.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "middle, next three\noff the middle.", 
            "dur": "1.64", 
            "start": "334.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And I&#39;ve got nine left, that was\nthe previous bottom pile.", 
            "dur": "3.41", 
            "start": "336.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s why now I get three from\nthe bottom, three from", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "339.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the bottom, three\nfrom the bottom.", 
            "dur": "1.16", 
            "start": "341.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So they end up going\ndown like that.", 
            "dur": "4.16", 
            "start": "343.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if you get some cards and\nyou start playing around with", 
            "dur": "2.3", 
            "start": "347.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this, within the final ordering\nit turns out from the", 
            "dur": "3.6", 
            "start": "349.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "very, very first time you put\nthem together this is the top,", 
            "dur": "3.92", 
            "start": "353.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the middle, the bottom.", 
            "dur": "1.46", 
            "start": "357"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The top, the middle,\nthe bottom.", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "358.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The top, the middle,\nthe bottom.", 
            "dur": "2.115", 
            "start": "359.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And don&#39;t lose too much sleep\nover exactly why this happens.", 
            "dur": "5.505", 
            "start": "361.875"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you get a pack of cards\nand deal it, you&#39;ll", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "367.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "start to see why.", 
            "dur": "0.99", 
            "start": "370.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And what you end up here is this\nis the ordering from the", 
            "dur": "3.24", 
            "start": "371.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "first time we dealt\nthe cards out.", 
            "dur": "3.15", 
            "start": "374.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That&#39;s the ordering from the\nsecond time we dealt the cards", 
            "dur": "3.22", 
            "start": "377.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "out, and that&#39;s the ordering\nfrom the third time we dealt", 
            "dur": "3.76", 
            "start": "380.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the cards out.", 
            "dur": "0.71", 
            "start": "384.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And to get it here at 10th,\nI can see that to get this", 
            "dur": "5.05", 
            "start": "385.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "position here it&#39;s\nthe 0th 0 first.", 
            "dur": "4.37", 
            "start": "390.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Or top, top, middle.", 
            "dur": "1.74", 
            "start": "394.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so each time Brady pointed\nto where his card was the", 
            "dur": "3.58", 
            "start": "396.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "first time I put that pile back\non top, the second time I", 
            "dur": "3.04", 
            "start": "399.91"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "put that pile back on top, The\nthird time I put that pile in", 
            "dur": "4.1", 
            "start": "402.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the middle.", 
            "dur": "0.91", 
            "start": "407.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The first time I put that\npile back on top.", 
            "dur": "5.5", 
            "start": "407.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The second time I put that\npile back on top.", 
            "dur": "6.207", 
            "start": "413.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The third time I put that\npile in the middle.", 
            "dur": "6.343", 
            "start": "419.667"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, Brady, do you want to\npick a different number?", 
            "dur": "2.465", 
            "start": "426.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: So say I told you my\nfavorite number was 13, what", 
            "dur": "3.675", 
            "start": "428.475"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would you have done?", 
            "dur": "0.58", 
            "start": "432.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: OK so 13, I need to put\n12 cards on top of that, and", 
            "dur": "4.1", 
            "start": "432.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "12 is one 9, one 3,\nand no units.", 
            "dur": "2.72", 
            "start": "436.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I&#39;m going to put\nthat on the top,", 
            "dur": "1.35", 
            "start": "439.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the middle, the middle.", 
            "dur": "0.78", 
            "start": "440.9"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "13 is, nine, 10, 11, 12, 13.", 
            "dur": "2.86", 
            "start": "441.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Yeah see?", 
            "dur": "0.51", 
            "start": "444.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "0, top, middle, middle.", 
            "dur": "2.98", 
            "start": "445.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the way I work it\nout is I&#39;m actually", 
            "dur": "2.52", 
            "start": "448.03"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "working it out in base-3.", 
            "dur": "2.03", 
            "start": "450.55"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because this whole trick uses\nbase-3 ternary numbers, which", 
            "dur": "3.35", 
            "start": "452.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I think are absolutely\namazing.", 
            "dur": "1.65", 
            "start": "455.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the first time you put the\npiles back together you&#39;re", 
            "dur": "2.76", 
            "start": "457.58"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "doing the units column of\nyour base-3 number.", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "460.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The next time you put them back\ntogether you doing 3&#39;s", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "462.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "column, and then the last time\nyou&#39;re doing the 9&#39;s column.", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "465.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so when you give me your\nnumber I work out that number", 
            "dur": "3.46", 
            "start": "467.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in base-3, and then that\ntells me how to put", 
            "dur": "2.483", 
            "start": "470.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the piles back together.", 
            "dur": "1.457", 
            "start": "473.333"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK so now we&#39;re going to redo\nthe very first trick I did in", 
            "dur": "4.51", 
            "start": "474.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "almost slow motion, in annotated\nmode if you will.", 
            "dur": "2.91", 
            "start": "479.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so you had a look at one\ncard, and then I started", 
            "dur": "3.33", 
            "start": "482.21"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "dealing these.", 
            "dur": "0.63", 
            "start": "485.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then I talked to you about\nyour favorite number,", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "486.17"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you said 10.", 
            "dur": "1.28", 
            "start": "487.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You&#39;re looking for the king of\nhearts, and I&#39;m thinking how", 
            "dur": "2.73", 
            "start": "489.15"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "am I going to get that\nking of hearts?", 
            "dur": "1.39", 
            "start": "491.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well I don&#39;t know\nwhat card it is.", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "493.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "How&#39;m I going to get\nwhatever the card", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "494.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is to the 10th position?", 
            "dur": "1.49", 
            "start": "495.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And 10, nine goes\ninto that once.", 
            "dur": "3.82", 
            "start": "497.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so I want to get\nnine cards on top.", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "500.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So I actually have to put it in\nthe top, the top, and then", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "503.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the middle.", 
            "dur": "1.3", 
            "start": "505.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So has the king of\nhearts gone past?", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "506.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Where was it?", 
            "dur": "0.855", 
            "start": "509.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: It was there.", 
            "dur": "0.535", 
            "start": "509.965"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: OK so I now know it has\nto go top, top, middle.", 
            "dur": "3.289", 
            "start": "510.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So when I pick them up from left\nto right-- these two I", 
            "dur": "2.371", 
            "start": "513.789"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "don&#39;t care about-- that can be\nbottom, that can be middle.", 
            "dur": "3.16", 
            "start": "516.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The king of hearts is in this\none, so it has to go on top.", 
            "dur": "4.17", 
            "start": "519.32"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which means it&#39;s going to\nbe one of the first nine", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "523.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to get dealt out.", 
            "dur": "0.94", 
            "start": "525.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so it&#39;s going to be either\nthe top card of the next", 
            "dur": "2.74", 
            "start": "526.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "piles, or the second card of\nthe next piles, which it", 
            "dur": "2.53", 
            "start": "529.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "happens to be, or\nthe third card.", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "531.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then the rest we actually\ndon&#39;t care about.", 
            "dur": "1.63", 
            "start": "533.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because those other two piles\nI know it wasn&#39;t in those.", 
            "dur": "3.19", 
            "start": "535.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "These are just padding to get it\ninto the correct position.", 
            "dur": "4.29", 
            "start": "538.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So now which one was it in?", 
            "dur": "2.19", 
            "start": "542.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The middle one?", 
            "dur": "0.81", 
            "start": "545.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "OK so again it&#39;s top,\ntop, middle.", 
            "dur": "2.11", 
            "start": "545.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it has to go top again.", 
            "dur": "1.09", 
            "start": "548.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if you watch, when I pick\nthem up I still pick them up", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "549.19"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the same order.", 
            "dur": "1.18", 
            "start": "551.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But I put them together\nin a different order.", 
            "dur": "1.91", 
            "start": "552.79"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So that goes on top, and then\nI&#39;ll get this last one, and", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "554.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I&#39;ll just shove it underneath.", 
            "dur": "1.73", 
            "start": "557.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So now I know it&#39;s on top.", 
            "dur": "1.72", 
            "start": "559"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact I know it&#39;s in the top\nthree of the top pile.", 
            "dur": "3.95", 
            "start": "560.72"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So when I go down this time\nit has to be the top", 
            "dur": "2.49", 
            "start": "564.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "card, there it is.", 
            "dur": "1.77", 
            "start": "567.16"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then the rest go on top, and\nthen the last time it has", 
            "dur": "3.15", 
            "start": "568.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to go in the middle.", 
            "dur": "0.85", 
            "start": "572.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so you can see what&#39;s\ngoing to happen now.", 
            "dur": "1.57", 
            "start": "572.93"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because if it goes in the middle\nit&#39;s going to get nine", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "574.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "cards put on top of it.", 
            "dur": "1.5", 
            "start": "575.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s going to be the top card in\nthe middle pile, it&#39;s going", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "577.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to be the 10th card.", 
            "dur": "1.14", 
            "start": "579.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it was in this one?", 
            "dur": "1.345", 
            "start": "580.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well how about that?", 
            "dur": "1.065", 
            "start": "582.265"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Pick that one up first, pick\nthat one up and put it", 
            "dur": "2.56", 
            "start": "583.33"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "underneath.", 
            "dur": "0.07", 
            "start": "585.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it was the middle one, put\nthat one underneath like that,", 
            "dur": "3.68", 
            "start": "585.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and so now it has to\nbe the 10th card.", 
            "dur": "2.1", 
            "start": "589.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "One, two, three, four, five,\nsix, seven, eight, nine, boom.", 
            "dur": "5.78", 
            "start": "591.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So in fact one way you can\nthink about it is I like", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "597.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "drawing a time versus\ncard height diagram.", 
            "dur": "6.78", 
            "start": "599.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So the first time you do\nit-- this is the first", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "606.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "time you deal out--", 
            "dur": "1.34", 
            "start": "608.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;ve got the bottom pack,\nyou&#39;ve got the middle pack,", 
            "dur": "3.73", 
            "start": "610.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and you&#39;ve got the\ntop pack when you", 
            "dur": "1.31", 
            "start": "613.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "put them back together.", 
            "dur": "1.08", 
            "start": "615.3"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And the reason I use 0, one, and\ntwo is actual units column", 
            "dur": "3.98", 
            "start": "616.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in ternary.", 
            "dur": "1.09", 
            "start": "620.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The second time you&#39;ve got the\nbottom pack, you&#39;ve got the", 
            "dur": "2.77", 
            "start": "621.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "middle pack, you&#39;ve got the top\npack, and again that&#39;s 0,", 
            "dur": "2.83", 
            "start": "624.22"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one, and two.", 
            "dur": "0.87", 
            "start": "627.05"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And that&#39;s the second\ntime you deal.", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "627.92"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And then the third time you\ndeal, again you&#39;ve got the", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "629.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bottom, the middle pack,\nand the top, and", 
            "dur": "2.895", 
            "start": "631.99"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that&#39;s 0, one, and two.", 
            "dur": "0.925", 
            "start": "634.885"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So there are the three\npacks when you", 
            "dur": "1.31", 
            "start": "635.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "put them back together.", 
            "dur": "1.11", 
            "start": "637.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And in fact this is your\nunits column, or", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "638.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that your 1&#39;s column.", 
            "dur": "1.97", 
            "start": "640.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "That there&#39;s your 3&#39;s\ncolumn, and that", 
            "dur": "2.39", 
            "start": "642.44"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "there&#39;s your 9&#39;s column.", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "644.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So if you want to put 15 on top,\nto get 15 you&#39;re going to", 
            "dur": "5.23", 
            "start": "647.53"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "need two 3&#39;s, one\n9, and no units.", 
            "dur": "5.1", 
            "start": "652.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So it&#39;s going to go top,\nbottom, middle.", 
            "dur": "2.37", 
            "start": "657.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To put 15 cards on top.", 
            "dur": "1.81", 
            "start": "660.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;ll end up being\nthe 16th card.", 
            "dur": "1.69", 
            "start": "662.04"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: If someone at home wants\nto do this trick do they", 
            "dur": "3.047", 
            "start": "663.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "have to be pretty\ngood at maths?", 
            "dur": "2.623", 
            "start": "666.777"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: You have two options.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "669.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You can either be pretty good\nat maths, or you can spend a", 
            "dur": "2.87", 
            "start": "670.78"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "lot of your free time practicing\nuntil your brain", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "673.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gets used to doing this.", 
            "dur": "1.17", 
            "start": "675.7"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Which to be fair, are both\nexactly the same thing.", 
            "dur": "2.98", 
            "start": "676.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Maths is all about practicing\nsomething, and developing a", 
            "dur": "2.82", 
            "start": "679.85"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "new way of thinking for your\nbrain to get used to it.", 
            "dur": "1.96", 
            "start": "682.67"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So either option, learn maths,\nof learn card tricks.", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "684.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You&#39;re ending up with the same\nskill set to be honest.", 
            "dur": "1.72", 
            "start": "687.63"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: You said at the start\nthis was your favorite trick", 
            "dur": "3", 
            "start": "689.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to some extent.", 
            "dur": "0.77", 
            "start": "692.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: It is.", 
            "dur": "1.48", 
            "start": "693.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "BRADY: There are\nlots of tricks.", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "694.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What is it about that one\nthat resonates with you?", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "695.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "MATT: People know the 21 card\ntrick, where you put it back", 
            "dur": "2.45", 
            "start": "701.89"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the middle each time, and\nthen it ends up being the", 
            "dur": "1.72", 
            "start": "704.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "middle card.", 
            "dur": "0.68", 
            "start": "706.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so people kind of\nknow that, but they", 
            "dur": "1.38", 
            "start": "706.74"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "don&#39;t know why it works.", 
            "dur": "1.16", 
            "start": "708.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Whereas this one you know why it\nworks, and then you can do", 
            "dur": "2.74", 
            "start": "709.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so much more with it.", 
            "dur": "0.93", 
            "start": "712.02"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And there&#39;s a huge difference in\nmath-- indeed in anything--", 
            "dur": "3.13", 
            "start": "712.95"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "between just memorizing the\nsteps so you know how to do", 
            "dur": "3.2", 
            "start": "716.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it, versus knowing why\nthose steps get you", 
            "dur": "2.7", 
            "start": "719.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "where you want to be.", 
            "dur": "0.86", 
            "start": "721.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so this utilizes the\nadvantage of knowing why the", 
            "dur": "4.36", 
            "start": "722.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "steps are doing something,\nand then you can", 
            "dur": "1.48", 
            "start": "727.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "tweak it as you go.", 
            "dur": "0.98", 
            "start": "728.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So instead of always putting it\nin the middle you can put", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "729.66"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it anywhere you want, because\nyou understand how it works.", 
            "dur": "4.7", 
            "start": "731.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because you&#39;re putting three\npiles back together three", 
            "dur": "2.21", 
            "start": "736.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "times there are 27 possible\narrangements of putting it", 
            "dur": "3.93", 
            "start": "738.41"
        }, 
        {
